Subject: Re: [T2] Steel Kadron Manifolds

Yes they are very bad regarding icing issues.  Another problem with steel
manifolds is that they have a propensity to leak (eventually).  I only use
aluminum manifolds with Kadrons, Webers, Dels, etc.
